font and text properties
for a good website along with colors, layout fonts alos play crucial role
ANy fonts in e world belongs to 5 Families
- serif - they will have strokes like TimesNewROman
- sans-serif - They dont have strokes like Arial
- monospace - Have same height for all elements like space mono
- Cursive - They have stylish letters kind of chained together like cederville
- Modern/ fantasy - Customised fonts and different fonts

Properties:
    font-family - typeface name, family name (eg: TimesNewROman, serif)
    font-weight: size (100-1000/bold.bolder) used for thickness
    font-style: italic/normal/oblique
    fornt-color: 
    text-align: center/left/right
    text-decoration: widht stple(solid.dotter/dahsed/wavy) color position(underline/overline/line-through)
    text-transform: uppercase/lowercase/capitalize
    text-shadow: x y z color(eg: 5px 6 px 5 px green)
    letter-spacing: size
    line-height: size


